# Regression for local-frame ("nose follows head") look controls.
#
# Forward is -W. Place a point on the ground, ahead and below. Then do the
# sequence that used to break: look RIGHT (XW), then look UP (YW).
#
# With LOCAL-frame rotation (the fix), look-up composes as fromYW * fromXW, so
# pitch turns about the camera's CURRENT axes. The old WORLD-frame Euler order
# was fromXW * fromYW, which lands the point at a different camera-space spot
# (≈ -2.46, -3.73, 0, 0). The exact 'assert at' below pins the local-frame
# result and so fails if the world-frame order ever creeps back.

point G 0 -2 0 -4
assert G below
assert G front

camera rotate xw 90
camera rotate yw 30

# Local-frame outcome of fromYW(30) * fromXW(90) applied to G:
assert at G -4 -1.7320508 0 1 1e-4
